itemDescription: Royal Air Force flying ace of the Second World War

wikipedia_page.main: Osgood Philip Villiers "Pedro" Hanbury,  (13 September 1917 – 3 June 1943) was a Royal Air Force flying ace of the Second World War. He had scored 11 victories before he was killed in action in 1943.

response: * June 3 – Osgood Hanbury, British pilot (killed on active service) (b. 1917)
* 3 June – Osgood Hanbury, pilot (killed on active service) (born 1917)
